<item>
            <title>[PIG-3090] Introduce a syntax to be able to easily refer to the previously defined relation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3090</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes I feel like swimming with ANTLRs. This particular feature isn&apos;t too hard to add... and supports syntax like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
a = load &apos;thing&apos; as (x:&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;);
b = foreach @ generate x;
c = foreach @ generate x;
d = foreach @ generate x;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have a patch, though I need to make sure it doesn&apos;t change anything (it shouldn&apos;t) and I need to add tests.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
